column3:
<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Zilekke can ill afford any delays.
Get the captivated courier's attention with a /poke.
Oh, hello there. You're an adventurer, right? Can I interest you in a job?
We're supposed to send out a shipment of electrope today, but the courier in charge appears to be taking her sweet time.

If our shipment falls behind schedule, it will bring Everkeep's factories to a screeching halt. I have to stay and handle things here, so could you go and tell the courier she has a job to do, please?

Given her obsession with technology, like as not, you'll find her wherever there's a clear view of the bucket elevator. She may not hear you approach, so give her a <UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>poke<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> if you need to.

The courier I speak of tends to linger in places where there's a clear view of the bucket elevator. She may not hear you approach, so give her a <UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>poke<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> if you need to.

The captivated courier does not appear to have noticed you. Perhaps a small <UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>poke<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> will get her attention.
Ah, you're here about the delivery─oh gods, the <Emphasis>delivery</Emphasis>! I was so enraptured watching the elevator that I must have lost track of time. Again...
I admit, I never get sick of seeing it in action. The hover cargo we use is great and all, but I mean, it can't possibly compare to the sheer <Emphasis>scale</Emphasis> of─
Gah, no, I can't start rambling now! Sorry, but I'd better get back to work!
Thanks for the assistance. Much as I can appreciate a fellow enthusiast of our technology, I can't allow it to impact our work.
The electrope we excavate here is a lifeline for Everkeep, and I do mean that quite literally.
This precious resource is used to create all manner of things, from daily necessities to heavy machinery, so you can imagine how a single hitch in the supply chain risks a ripple effect of chaos.
At any rate, here's a little something for your trouble.
